<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFFADF738FF366B74FEC1E0A0" blockId="25.[164,779,1113,1227]" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FF366B74FDABE005" box="[164,618,1113,1134]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">
Etymology: 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFADF738FEB86B74FDABE005" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="2009" box="[298,618,1113,1134]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="speciosa" subSpecies="celineata">Grammia speciosa celineata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is a combination of the names 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFADF738FEEE6B5AFE71E0E7" box="[380,432,1143,1164]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Callarctia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="celia">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FEEE6B5AFE71E0E7" box="[380,432,1143,1164]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">celia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FE7D6B5AFDFFE0E7" box="[495,574,1143,1164]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">lineata</emphasis>
, the unpublished name originally proposed for this taxon by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFADF738FD576BBBFF3DE0A0" author="Smith ME" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" refId="ref64404" refString="Smith ME. 1938 a. A revision of the genus Apantesis Walker (Lepidoptera, Arctiidae). Unpublished Ph. D. thesis. Urbana: University of Illinois." type="book" year="1938">Smith (1938a)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFFADF738FF366BD9FD90E213" blockId="25.[164,779,1267,1656]" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FF366BD9FD42E163" box="[164,643,1267,1289]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">
Diagnosis: 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFADF738FEBC6BD9FD42E163" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="2009" box="[302,643,1267,1289]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="speciosa" subSpecies="celineata">Grammia speciosa celineata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is unique among 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFADF738FF6A6A3FFE95E14C" authorityName="CELINEATA SCHMIDT" authorityYear="2009" box="[248,340,1298,1319]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FF6A6A3FFE95E14C" box="[248,340,1298,1319]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
populations in that the abdomen and hindwing can be entirely black, the forewing vein lines can be reduced or absent, and forms expressing fragmentary medial and postmedial bands are more common. The limited available data show that 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FD466AA0FEC8E1AB" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">G. s. celineata</emphasis>
is diurnal. Forms exhibiting both loss of vein lines and expression of forewing bands can be similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFADF738FF5A6AC5FEF9E195" box="[200,312,1512,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="margo">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FF5A6AC5FEF9E195" box="[200,312,1512,1534]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">G. margo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FE136AC5FE27E196" box="[385,486,1512,1533]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">celineata</emphasis>
has larger eyes, longer antennal rami, is larger overall, and flies later in the year (mid June onwards vs. late May to early June) compared to 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFADF738FEAD6969FE46E232" box="[319,391,1604,1625]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="margo">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FEAD6969FE46E232" box="[319,391,1604,1625]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">margo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. See diagnosis under 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFADF738FD006969FF15E21C" baseAuthorityName="Schmidt" baseAuthorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Apantesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virguncula">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FD006969FF15E21C" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">G. virguncula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for comparison to other species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFFADF738FF36698FFB56E0FB" blockId="25.[164,779,1697,1903]" lastBlockId="25.[826,1441,198,1168]" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FF36698FFEB1E2DD" box="[164,368,1697,1719]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">Description: Head</emphasis>
– Palps black, frons and vertex pale to yellowish buff; male antennae moderately bipectinate, rami averaging 3.18 ¥ 10 
<superScript id="7C659BA4FFADF738FD9969F1FDDAE283" attach="left" box="[523,539,1756,1769]" fontSize="5" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">
- 
<quantity id="4CE89B09FFADF738FD8169F1FDDAE283" box="[531,539,1756,1768]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" unit="mm" value="1.0">1</quantity>
</superScript>
mm, (
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FDFA69F2FDBDE29F" box="[616,636,1759,1780]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">N</emphasis>
= 8); female antennae moderately biserrate; dorsal scales dark brown to black; eyes slightly reduced, mean diameter 7.1 ¥ 10 
<superScript id="7C659BA4FFADF738FF6F6815FECCE32F" attach="left" box="[253,269,1848,1861]" fontSize="5" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">
- 
<quantity id="4CE89B09FFADF738FE976815FECCE32F" box="[261,269,1848,1860]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" unit="mm" value="1.0">1</quantity>
</superScript>
mm. 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FEC26817FE63E324" box="[336,418,1850,1871]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">Thorax</emphasis>
– Vestiture black with pale to yellowish buff borders on vertex, patagia, and tegulae; black ventrally, base of coxa and distal area usually with yellowish buff scales; coxa and femur black centrally, yellow at base and apex, giving striped appearance, or entirely dark brown – black; tibia and tarsus pale buff dorsally, black ventrally. 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FB5E6E6DFAF7E53E" box="[1228,1334,320,341]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">Abdomen</emphasis>
– Dorsal ground colour yellow, pale buff near apex; medial and lateral markings black, medial line broad; pale buff ventrally, lateral black markings broad but not confluent at midline; occasionally entirely black ventrally and dorsally. 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FC4A6EF7FB83E584" box="[984,1090,474,495]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">Forewing</emphasis>
– Male forewing length averaging 
<quantity id="4CE89B09FFADF738FC1B6ED5FC2DE666" box="[905,1004,504,526]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.51" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" unit="mm" value="15.1">15.1 mm</quantity>
(
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FB966ED4FBD9E665" box="[1028,1048,505,526]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">N</emphasis>
= 
<specimenCount id="9D16FD65FFADF738FBA66ED5FB59E665" box="[1076,1176,504,526]" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" type="male">6 males</specimenCount>
); black dorsally, vein lines complete; reduced to distal half, or absent; lines and bands yellowish; rarely pale buff; cubital vein line not thickened; medial band usually absent, occasionally present as bar in discal cell; fragmentary postmedial band often present as bar across distal end of discal cell, and/or below end of discal cell; subterminal band complete; fringe and anal margin concolourous with pale markings, costal margin entirely pale, sometimes reduced to basal half; ventral markings similar, but dark markings with a paler yellowish cast; sexes similar. 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FBB56C65FB58E736" box="[1063,1177,840,861]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">Hindwing</emphasis>
– Ground colour dull yellow or entirely black; black markings highly variable in extent, but antemedial, medial, postmedial, and subterminal elements nearly always present, and often confluent to the point where yellow is reduced to irregular central area; entirely black form relatively common in both sexes (seven of 
<specimenCount id="9D16FD65FFADF738FB7C6B2DFA54E07D" box="[1262,1429,1024,1046]" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" type="generic">30 specimens</specimenCount>
); ventral markings similar, but dark markings with a paler yellowish cast; sexes similar. 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FB7B6B10FA95E039" box="[1257,1364,1085,1106]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">Genitalia</emphasis>
– not distinguishable from 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFADF738FBD16B71FB0BE01A" authorityName="CELINEATA SCHMIDT" authorityYear="2009" box="[1091,1226,1116,1137]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FBD16B71FB0BE01A" box="[1091,1226,1116,1137]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">G. speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
structurally; see description under 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFADF738FB826B56FB4EE0FB" authorityName="CELINEATA SCHMIDT" authorityYear="2009" box="[1040,1167,1147,1168]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FB826B56FB4EE0FB" box="[1040,1167,1147,1168]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">G. speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFFADF738FCA86B95FB81E10C" blockId="25.[826,1441,1208,1383]" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FCA86B95FC54E0A6" box="[826,917,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">Biology:</emphasis>
Collection dates for 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFADF738FB376B95FA60E0A6" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="2009" box="[1189,1441,1208,1229]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="speciosa" subSpecies="celineata">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FB376B95FA60E0A6" box="[1189,1441,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">G. speciosa celineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
range from mid June to August, with most records from late June. Although the eyes are not strongly reduced in size, 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FB9F6A39FB7EE143" box="[1037,1215,1299,1321]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">G. s. celineata</emphasis>
males fly in late afternoon in spruce bogs, and are not known to come to light (pers. observ.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFFADF738FCA86AA3FA83E18A" blockId="25.[826,1441,1422,1505]" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FCA86AA3FC0DE1C8" box="[826,972,1422,1443]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">Distribution:</emphasis>
Occurs in the foothills and mountains of southern and central 
<collectionCode id="ED01AE29FFADF738FBA56A80FB9CE1A9" box="[1079,1117,1453,1474]" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">AB</collectionCode>
, and possibly further north in the cordilleran region of western 
<collectingCountry id="F307767CFFADF738FB716AE6FAFFE18A" box="[1251,1342,1483,1505]" name="Canada" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">Canada</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFFADF73BFCA86925FEEEE5BA" blockId="25.[826,1441,1544,1903]" lastBlockId="26.[144,759,198,801]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="533" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FCA86925FC67E276" box="[826,934,1544,1565]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">Remarks:</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="54AB884EFFADF738FC766924FBD4E275" box="[996,1045,1545,1566]" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">type</typeStatus>
series of 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FB1B6925FB2FE276" box="[1161,1262,1544,1565]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">celineata</emphasis>
is restricted to specimens from the 
<collectionCode id="ED01AE29FFADF738FBB8690AFB8FE257" box="[1066,1102,1575,1596]" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">AB</collectionCode>
foothills, as specimens from northern BC, 
<collectionCode id="ED01AE29FFADF738FC4C696BFBC0E230" box="[990,1025,1606,1627]" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">YT</collectionCode>
, and AK are few and may not represent this taxon, although provisionally included as 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFADF738FCA869AEFC57E2F3" authorityName="CELINEATA SCHMIDT" authorityYear="2009" box="[826,918,1667,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FCA869AEFC57E2F3" box="[826,918,1667,1688]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
here. 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFADF738FC7669AEFAE9E2F3" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="2009" box="[996,1320,1667,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="speciosa" subSpecies="celineata">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FC7669AEFAE9E2F3" box="[996,1320,1667,1688]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">Grammia speciosa celineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was associated with 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFADF738FC51698FFBEFE2DC" box="[963,1070,1698,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="margo">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FC51698FFBEFE2DC" box="[963,1070,1698,1719]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">G. margo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFADF738FBF9698FFB3BE2DD" authorityName="stat." authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Hy. Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[1131,1274,1697,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="franconia">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FBF9698FFB3BE2DD" box="[1131,1274,1697,1719]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">G. franconia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFADF738FABF698FFA42E2DD" box="[1325,1411,1697,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Callarctia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="celia">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FABF698FFA42E2DD" box="[1325,1411,1697,1719]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">G. celia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of auth.) by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFADF738FC2369EDFB93E2BE" author="Smith ME" box="[945,1106,1728,1750]" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" refId="ref64404" refString="Smith ME. 1938 a. A revision of the genus Apantesis Walker (Lepidoptera, Arctiidae). Unpublished Ph. D. thesis. Urbana: University of Illinois." type="book" year="1938">Smith (1938a</bibRefCitation>
, b), who believed it to be a form of ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFADF738FC3069F3FC17E298" box="[930,982,1758,1779]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Callarctia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="celia">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FC3069F3FC17E298" box="[930,982,1758,1779]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">celia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ with lined forewings. Examination of additional specimens from the vicinity of the 
<typeStatus id="54AB884EFFADF738FAE269D0FA60E379" box="[1392,1441,1789,1810]" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FC206831FBD6E35A" box="[946,1047,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">celineata</emphasis>
show variation to typical 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFADF738FAD76831FA60E35A" authorityName="CELINEATA SCHMIDT" authorityYear="2009" box="[1349,1441,1820,1841]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFADF738FAD76831FA60E35A" box="[1349,1441,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="532">speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
wing pattern in specimens collected at the same locality and the same date as unlined forms. The antennal structure, eye size, habitat, and flight time are also consistent with 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFAEF73BFED86FC8FE67E491" authorityName="CELINEATA SCHMIDT" authorityYear="2009" box="[330,422,229,250]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFAEF73BFED86FC8FE67E491" box="[330,422,229,250]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="533">speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and differ from the 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFAEF73BFD0D6FC8FF3CE573" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="533">
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFAEF73BFD0D6FC8FD28E491" box="[671,745,229,250]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="margo">margo</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFAEF73BFF026E2EFF3CE573" authorityName="stat." authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Hy. Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[144,253,259,280]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="franconia">franconia</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
group. The relationship of 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFAEF73BFDAA6E2EFD77E572" authorityName="CELINEATA SCHMIDT" authorityYear="2009" box="[568,694,259,281]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFAEF73BFDAA6E2EFD77E572" box="[568,694,259,281]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="533">G. speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFAEF73BFD4E6E2EFECAE55C" baseAuthorityName="Schmidt" baseAuthorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Apantesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virguncula">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFAEF73BFD4E6E2EFECAE55C" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="533">G. virguncula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
populations where they come into contact is unclear – typical 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFAEF73BFE166E6CFDE4E53E" baseAuthorityName="Schmidt" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[388,549,320,342]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Apantesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virguncula">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFAEF73BFE166E6CFDE4E53E" box="[388,549,320,342]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="533">G. virguncula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in prairie and montane regions adjacent to populations of 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFAEF73BFF026E53FEF0E5F9" box="[144,305,381,403]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="533">G. s. celineata</emphasis>
in the 
<collectionCode id="ED01AE29FFAEF73BFE176E53FE68E5F8" box="[389,425,382,403]" pageId="26" pageNumber="533">AB</collectionCode>
foothills, as discussed under ‘Remarks’ for 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFAEF73BFEDA6EB1FE12E5D9" authorityName="CELINEATA SCHMIDT" authorityYear="2009" box="[328,467,412,434]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFAEF73BFEDA6EB1FE12E5D9" box="[328,467,412,434]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="533">G. speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The situation awaits further study.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFFAEF73BFF3A6EF4FE78E74A" blockId="26.[144,759,198,801]" pageId="26" pageNumber="533">
Although this taxon was first collected over a century ago by AB’s foremost pioneer lepidopterist, Frederic H. Wolley Dod, its taxonomic affinity has remained unclear (and perhaps still is!). The range of phenotypes expressed by 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFAEF73BFE286D79FD9FE602" box="[442,606,596,617]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="533">G. s. celineata</emphasis>
, particularly evident in a series of Bragg Creek specimens reared by F. Sperling, may be indicative of introgression with other 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFAEF73BFF4A6D9DFE62E6AE" box="[216,419,687,709]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFAEF73BFF4A6D9DFE87E6AE" box="[216,326,688,709]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="533">Grammia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(such as 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFAEF73BFD8D6D9DFD67E6AF" baseAuthorityName="Stretch" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[543,678,687,709]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFAEF73BFD8D6D9DFD67E6AF" box="[543,678,687,709]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="533">G. elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), or it may represent a regional genetic variation towards melanism wherein the paler fore- and hindwing patterns are lost or reduced.
</paragraph>
